  </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ideas for good characters...:-)</span><hr size=1> ...A Half-Elf Druid of Karana, Sarhea's former life.<br>
(I don't think she's a druid anymore, but I may be<br>
really stupid.)  Verisha, saddened by the great<br>
pride and elitist attitudes of some Feir'Dal, wishes<br>
to prove that Tunare isn't the ONLY Druid deity <br>
who has any real power.  She admires Karana's force.<br>
(If ever she makes 20, she'll be Verisha Karahni.)<br>
<br>
Releesha, a Halfling Cleric Lass of Bristlebane.  <br>
She sneaks up on Norrath like a peridot-green,<br>
mischievous shadow.  She flips guards upside-down,<br>
pokes people while Hiding, and knows that real<br>
death in Norrath, for the players, is merely a joke.<br>
Some exp may be lost, but the player doesn't<br>
get wiped out totally like in a character wipe.<br>
(If she ever hits 20, she'll be Releesha Fromdeth.)<br>
<br>
Duficia (read: dufus), a really, um, stupid Dwarf Cleric.<br>
She follows Brell, yeah...getting herself drunk until<br>
her WIS is like, 12.  She's not a very good Cleric,<br>
but at least the wiser Dwarf Priests can count on<br>
Duficia for a good laugh.  She's good in a group--<br>
for melee.  Duficia is ALWAYS doing stuff wrong!<br>
<br>
(Duficia is also what I feel like a lot of times in EQ)<br>
